{"lemma": "حَصِيرٌ", "slug": "حَصِيرٌ", "root": "ح.ص.ر", "root_slug": "ح-ص-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-ص-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "حَصِير", "root": "حصر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n8220"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "mat", "fa": "حصیر", "ur": "حصیر", "tr": "hasır", "id": "tikar", "bn": "মাদুর", "es": "esterilla", "fr": "nattes", "de": "Matte", "ru": "циновка", "zh": "席子"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "mat"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ħa.sˤiːr/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n8220", "headword_ar": "حَصِيرٌ", "root": "HSr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHoSuwrN", "text_ar": "مَحْصُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places: ―         -b2-  and see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaSirN", "text_ar": "حَصِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in four places. ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A king:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, K:) because he is secluded: (S, A:) or because he prevents those who have access to him. (TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A prison;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HiSaArN", "text_ar": "حِصَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) So [accord. to some] in the Kur xvii. 8. (S, ISd.)       -A3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A mat woven of reeds"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of rushes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (Msb, K) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of palm-leaves;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IDrd and K voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ta*ar~aEa", "text_ar": "تَذَرَّعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", &c.;) syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAriy~apN", "text_ar": "بَارِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb, K;) vulgarly ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaSiyrapN", "text_ar": "حَصِيرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing woven,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiyfapN", "text_ar": "سَفِيفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the L and TA erroneously written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sqyfh", "text_ar": "سقيفه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "barodiY~", "text_ar": "بَرْدِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "papyrus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asal", "text_ar": "اَسَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rushes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and then spread upon the ground like a carpet:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuSurN", "text_ar": "حُصُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA) and, by contraction,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuSorN", "text_ar": "حُصْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) Hence the prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asiyrN EalaY HaSiyrK", "text_ar": "اَسِيرٌ عَلَى حَصِيرٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A captive upon a mat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAtu AlHaSiyri", "text_ar": "بَنَاتُ الحَصِيرِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Bugs;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baq~N", "text_ar": "بَقٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bq", "text_ar": "بق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything woven."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A garment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of cloth, ornamented and variegated, which, when spread out, captivates hearts in a manner peculiar to it, by its beauty."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) So, accord. to some, in the trad. of Hodheyfeh,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tuEoraDu", "text_ar": "تُعْرَضُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfitanu EalaY Alquluwbi EaroDa AlHaSiyri", "text_ar": "الفِتَنُ عَلَى القُلُوبِ عَرْضَ الحَصِيرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[expl. in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ErD", "text_ar": "عرض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", conj. 1]. (B.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bed;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing spread to lie upon;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though it were a mat: so, accord. to El-Hasan, in the Kur xvii. 8, referred to above. (TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A sitting-place;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majolisN", "text_ar": "مَجْلِسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K, and so in two copies of the A:) MF thinks it to be a mistake for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHobisN", "text_ar": "مَحْبِسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a prison,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place of confinement"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "surface of the ground:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K:) whence, accord. to some, it is applied to that which is spread upon the ground [i. e. a mat]: (TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHoSirapN", "text_ar": "اَحْصِرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuSurN", "text_ar": "حُصُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Water."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) [Perhaps because its surface, when rippled by the wind, is likened to a thing woven: see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nasaja", "text_ar": "نَسَجَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b8-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diversified wavy marks, streaks,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grain,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firinod", "text_ar": "فِرِنْد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) of a sword, (K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "resembling the tracks"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of ants: (TA:) or its"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaSiyraAni", "text_ar": "حَصِيرَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are its"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two sides."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA.) ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A road,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "way."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, K.) ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A row"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of men, and of other things. (K.) ―         -b11-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain vein extending across upon the side of a beast, towards the belly:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) so, accord. to some, in the trad. of Hodheyfeh mentioned above: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a portion of flesh so situate;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the shoulder-blade to the flank;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaSiyrapN", "text_ar": "حَصِيرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", explained in the K as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a portion of flesh lying across in the side of a horse, which one sees when he is made lean by scanty food:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or the former signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sinew that"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 584}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is between the part called the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SifaAq", "text_ar": "صِفَاق"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the part where the false ribs end;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is the end of the side:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "part that is between the vein that appears in the side of the camel and horse, lying across, and what is above it, to the part where the side terminates:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S:) or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HSyr", "text_ar": "حصير"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the side is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what appears of the upper parts of the ribs."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-Es-Seed.) ―         -b12-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "itself. (Az, S, K.) Hence the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAb~apN EariyDu AlHaSiyrayoni", "text_ar": "دَابَّةٌ عَرِيضُ الحَصِيرَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A beast having wide sides."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^awojaEa A@ll~`hu HaSiyrayohi", "text_ar": "اَوْجَعَ ا@للّٰهُ حَصِيرَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God make his sides to ache;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may he be severely beaten."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.) A certain elegant scholar says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^av~ara HaSiyru AlHaSiyri fiY HaSiyri", "text_ar": "اَثَّرَ حَصِيرُ الحَصِيرِ فِى حَصِيرِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaSiyri", "text_ar": "الحَصِيرِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The mat of the prison made marks upon the side of the king."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MF.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "A", "K", "Msb", "TA", "As"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}